- 'Well-functioning thermometers' refers to sensors with an 'active' status; 
- 'Heat signatures' are represented by temperature readings in degrees Celsius; 
- 'Upkeep frequencies' correspond to the number of maintenance events; 
- 'Burning the brightest' means having an average temperature greater than 20 degrees Celsius.

- Active sensors are those that are currently operational and available for use; 
- Calibration and replacement are types of maintenance that involve adjusting the sensor to ensure accurate readings or replacing it with a new one, respectively; 
- The time frame of "the past year" refers to the period from the current date to one year prior.
